Use the standard library
This is how to can_arrange of arr:
   Remember that n is arr's length
   Remember that i is 0
   Remember that answer is -1
   Do this (diff of n and 1) times:
      When item i in arr is more than item (sum of i and 1) in arr, then:
         Remember that answer is sum of i and 1
         Leave the loop
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is answer
Now you know

>>> can_arrange of [1, 2, 4, 3, 5]
3
>>> can_arrange of [1, 2, 3]
-1
>>> can_arrange of [1, 2, 4, 3, 5]
3